so what do you do?

878
00:27:58,960 --> 00:27:59,720
y'all know what I did

879
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,620
I started to copy them

880
00:28:01,620 --> 00:28:04,240
even though I had no idea

881
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:05,420
what any of them were doing

882
00:28:05,420 --> 00:28:07,420
and the next year

883
00:28:07,420 --> 00:28:12,320
I made 12 million dollars in profit

884
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:16,340
but that year there was a lot of public discontent

885
00:28:16,340 --> 00:28:17,900
about the pay and the bankers bonuses

886
00:28:17,900 --> 00:28:20,120
the bankers who in their eyes

887
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,220
had ruined the global economy

888
00:28:21,220 --> 00:28:24,400
and I sat there on the trading floor

889
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:27,100
and I was still a poor boy

890
00:28:27,100 --> 00:28:29,180
sleeping on broken mattresses

891
00:28:29,180 --> 00:28:31,540
still showering with a hose in my parents' bathtub

892
00:28:31,540 --> 00:28:33,920
only now surrounded by millionaires

893
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:36,000
as Gordon Brown

894
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:37,940
the then Prime Minister of my country

895
00:28:37,940 --> 00:28:39,900
said he would tax the bankers

896
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:41,480
he would tax their bonuses

897
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:43,660
and I looked around

898
00:28:43,660 --> 00:28:45,480
and the millionaires around me

899
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:46,420
were laughing

900
00:28:46,420 --> 00:28:48,480
and one of them grabbed my shoulder

901
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:48,980
and he said

902
00:28:48,980 --> 00:28:50,660
don't worry Gary

903
00:28:50,660 --> 00:28:52,380
they'll never tax us

904
00:28:52,380 --> 00:28:55,060
and I took a big breath in

905
00:28:55,060 --> 00:28:56,600
and I breathed it all out

906
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,760
what does that mean?

907
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:00,800
what would you do?

908
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:06,280
I waited for my first big bonus

909
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:10,420
I was expecting it to be 100,000 pounds

910
00:29:10,420 --> 00:29:13,480
at that time in my life

911
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:16,040
100,000 pounds was the biggest sum of money

912
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:16,820
that I could imagine

913
00:29:16,820 --> 00:29:19,900
my dad had worked his whole life

914
00:29:19,900 --> 00:29:21,800
for 20,000 pounds a year

915
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:25,080
what I got

916
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:28,380
was 395,000 pounds

917
00:29:28,380 --> 00:29:31,660
what does that mean?

918
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:33,860
what would you do?

919
00:29:33,860 --> 00:29:37,820
you know when I was in sixth form

920
00:29:37,820 --> 00:29:40,320
I would skip lunch to save money

921
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:43,180
my friend Asad

922
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:44,860
would sometimes feel bad for me

923
00:29:44,860 --> 00:29:46,780
and he'd buy me a burger meal

924
00:29:46,780 --> 00:29:48,180
from a shop called Pizza King

925
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:49,280
around the corner from the school

926
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:51,280
and I'd have it with burger sauce

927
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:53,640
you know that orange sauce

928
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:56,460
when I was at uni for lunch

929
00:29:56,460 --> 00:29:58,780
I would buy two scotch eggs from Tesco

930
00:29:58,780 --> 00:30:00,500
for 75p

931
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:02,380
every day for two years

932
00:30:02,380 --> 00:30:04,540
and then one day

933
00:30:04,540 --> 00:30:06,400
when I had just turned 23

934
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:10,000
someone gave me 395,000 pounds

935
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:12,720
what does that mean?

936
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:14,880
what would you do?

937
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:17,820
I wanted more

938
00:30:17,820 --> 00:30:21,040
the next year, 2010

939
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:23,100
I copied everyone again

940
00:30:23,100 --> 00:30:23,880
and it didn't work

941
00:30:23,880 --> 00:30:25,860
for the first time ever

942
00:30:25,860 --> 00:30:26,480
I lost money

943
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,760
I lost 8 million dollars

944
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:29,900
in one single week

945
00:30:29,900 --> 00:30:31,300
when the Swiss National Bank

946
00:30:31,300 --> 00:30:33,159
unexpectedly cut its interest rates

947
00:30:33,159 --> 00:30:34,680
to negative 4.5%

948
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:37,960
that was the first time ever

949
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,100
that it occurred to me

950
00:30:39,100 --> 00:30:41,720
that maybe LSE had done me a disservice

951
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:44,540
maybe memorising answers

952
00:30:44,540 --> 00:30:46,460
and not actually learning anything

953
00:30:46,460 --> 00:30:47,960
wasn't really that useful

954
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:50,220
maybe you did need to know

955
00:30:50,220 --> 00:30:51,440
about the economy after all

956
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:53,300
who knew?

957
00:30:53,300 --> 00:30:56,960
but that moment began an obsession

958
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:57,379
for me

959
00:30:57,379 --> 00:31:00,100
an obsession that continues today

960
00:31:00,100 --> 00:31:03,360
an obsession to understand the economy

961
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:06,740
why did I want to understand the economy?

962
00:31:08,460 --> 00:31:09,820
because I wanted to make money

963
00:31:09,820 --> 00:31:13,139
what does that mean?

964
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:15,600
what would you do?

965
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:18,640
so around about that time

966
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:19,520
late 2010

967
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:20,760
early 2011

968
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:22,820
I was starting to understand

969
00:31:22,820 --> 00:31:24,420
that nobody had any idea

970
00:31:24,420 --> 00:31:25,100
what they were doing

971
00:31:25,100 --> 00:31:28,860
see my job was to predict interest rates

972
00:31:28,860 --> 00:31:31,280
to summarise quite aggressively

973
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:33,000
interest rates go down

974
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,000
when the economy is weak

975
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,460
and up when the economy is strong

976
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:39,180
by the beginning of 2011

977
00:31:39,180 --> 00:31:41,180
I had witnessed markets

978
00:31:41,180 --> 00:31:42,440
predict interest rates

979
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:43,380
completely incorrectly

980
00:31:43,380 --> 00:31:44,300
for three years

981
00:31:44,300 --> 00:31:47,640
see cutting interest rates to zero

982
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,420
is supposed to stimulate the economy

983
00:31:49,420 --> 00:31:51,600
that's what we are taught at university

984
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:55,760
due to the massive interest rate cuts in 2008

985
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:58,340
economists all expected the economy

986
00:31:58,340 --> 00:32:00,560
to bounce back sharply in 2009

987
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:02,300
it didn't

988
00:32:02,300 --> 00:32:04,140
after that

989
00:32:04,140 --> 00:32:05,920
economists expected the same thing

990
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:07,080
to happen in 2010

991
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:09,080
it didn't

992
00:32:09,180 --> 00:32:10,980
I didn't know at the time

993
00:32:10,980 --> 00:32:12,480
but this pattern would actually continue

994
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:13,560
for 13 years

995
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:15,840
economists in the UK

996
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:18,660
predicted economic and interest rate recovery

997
00:32:18,660 --> 00:32:19,920
every single year

998
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:22,520
from 2009 to 2020

999
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:24,540
in 2020

1000
00:32:24,540 --> 00:32:26,300
they finally agreed

1001
00:32:26,300 --> 00:32:28,280
that interest rates would actually

1002
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:29,460
never go up again

1003
00:32:29,460 --> 00:32:32,020
what does that mean?

1004
00:32:34,460 --> 00:32:35,180
anyway look

1005
00:32:35,180 --> 00:32:36,300
I didn't know this at that time

1006
00:32:36,300 --> 00:32:37,680
all I knew then

1007
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:38,720
was that the traders

1008
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:39,760
and the economists

1009
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:41,080
have been wrong for three years

1010
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:43,940
they were predicting economic recoveries

1011
00:32:43,940 --> 00:32:44,600
that won't happen

1012
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,520
why?

1013
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:46,560
why?

1014
00:32:51,940 --> 00:32:52,900
in my opinion

1015
00:32:52,900 --> 00:32:55,180
the reason those traders

1016
00:32:55,180 --> 00:32:55,900
and economists

1017
00:32:55,900 --> 00:32:57,900
thought the economy would get better

1018
00:32:57,900 --> 00:32:59,400
every single year

1019
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:01,260
from 2008 up to now

1020
00:33:01,260 --> 00:33:02,900
is because for them

1021
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:04,380
it did get better

1022
00:33:04,380 --> 00:33:06,680
for the rich

1023
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:07,960
life got better

1024
00:33:07,960 --> 00:33:08,420
and better

1025
00:33:08,420 --> 00:33:08,860
and better

1026
00:33:08,860 --> 00:33:11,340
pretty much every single year

1027
00:33:11,340 --> 00:33:13,220
from 2008 up to now

1028
00:33:13,220 --> 00:33:16,640
so why did interest rates stay at zero

1029
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:19,080
that whole decade

1030
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,900
after 2010

1031
00:33:20,900 --> 00:33:29,340
I had an idea

1032
00:33:29,340 --> 00:33:29,360
I had an idea

1033
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:33,440
the reason interest rates

1034
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:34,820
are supposed to stimulate the economy

1035
00:33:34,820 --> 00:33:37,360
is because they're supposed to get you spending

1036
00:33:37,360 --> 00:33:40,680
but people weren't spending

1037
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:43,880
and I asked a few of the traders

1038
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:44,520
why

1039
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:45,220
and they said

1040
00:33:45,220 --> 00:33:45,580
you know

1041
00:33:45,580 --> 00:33:48,100
there's problems with the banking sector

1042
00:33:48,100 --> 00:33:48,960
which are fixed now

1043
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,960
there's problems with confidence

1044
00:33:50,960 --> 00:33:51,720
that are fixed now

1045
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:55,160
one time I asked an Oxford economics professor

1046
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:56,860
why did you think

1047
00:33:56,860 --> 00:33:59,540
spending was so weak

1048
00:33:59,540 --> 00:34:00,400
after 2008?

1049
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:02,460
he said

1050
00:34:02,460 --> 00:34:04,440
there was an exogenous shock

1051
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:06,080
to consumption savings preferences

1052
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:10,680
so I decided

1053
00:34:10,680 --> 00:34:12,520
to do something radical

1054
00:34:12,520 --> 00:34:14,020
in the world of economics

1055
00:34:14,020 --> 00:34:16,139
I went out

1056
00:34:16,139 --> 00:34:17,320
and I started asking people

1057
00:34:17,320 --> 00:34:20,160
have you had an exogenous shock

1058
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:21,560
to your consumption savings preferences

1059
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:25,920
I'm going to read you a passage

1060
00:34:25,920 --> 00:34:26,500
from my book

1061
00:34:26,500 --> 00:34:28,139
because my publicist will be delighted

1062
00:34:28,139 --> 00:34:30,799
this is what people said

1063
00:34:30,799 --> 00:34:32,960
when I asked them

1064
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:35,279
why they weren't spending more money

1065
00:34:35,279 --> 00:34:39,239
I asked Harry Sambi

1066
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:42,219
Harry was still just a kid

1067
00:34:42,219 --> 00:34:45,739
Harry had holes in his shoes

1068
00:34:45,739 --> 00:34:48,100
and he was jumping over the barriers

1069
00:34:48,100 --> 00:34:48,940
on the tube

1070
00:34:48,940 --> 00:34:50,020
to save costs

1071
00:34:50,020 --> 00:34:52,920
that's why he didn't spend money

1072
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:55,299
I asked Asad

1073
00:34:55,299 --> 00:34:57,520
Asad said his mum

1074
00:34:57,520 --> 00:34:58,880
had sold the family home

1075
00:34:58,880 --> 00:35:00,200
to support him and his sisters

1076
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:02,680
and now he was sleeping on the sofa

1077
00:35:02,680 --> 00:35:04,340
to try and save up a deposit

1078
00:35:04,340 --> 00:35:07,420
that's why they didn't spend money

1079
00:35:07,420 --> 00:35:10,440
I asked Aidan

1080
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:13,380
Aidan's mum had lost her job

1081
00:35:13,380 --> 00:35:14,940
and hadn't been able to get a new rate

1082
00:35:14,940 --> 00:35:15,460
on the mortgage

1083
00:35:15,460 --> 00:35:18,420
now the monthly payments were sky high

1084
00:35:18,420 --> 00:35:20,920
and Aidan was having to pay them himself

1085
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:23,920
that's why they didn't spend money

1086
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:26,860
they were losing their homes

1087
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:29,800
I hadn't even noticed

1088
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:37,680
so you realise

1089
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:40,080
that the hundreds of billions of pounds

1090
00:35:40,080 --> 00:35:41,640
the importance of the economy

1091
00:35:41,640 --> 00:35:43,020
by governments and central banks

1092
00:35:43,020 --> 00:35:44,920
aren't doing anything

1093
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:46,680
to protect ordinary people

1094
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:50,140
very shortly after that

1095
00:35:50,140 --> 00:35:51,980
you recognise that basically

1096
00:35:51,980 --> 00:35:52,700
every government

1097
00:35:52,700 --> 00:35:54,700
in the world

1098
00:35:54,700 --> 00:35:55,939
is bankrupt

1099
00:35:55,939 --> 00:35:57,640
Spain

1100
00:35:57,640 --> 00:35:58,819
Italy

1101
00:35:58,819 --> 00:36:00,060
Portugal

1102
00:36:00,060 --> 00:36:01,180
Greece

1103
00:36:01,180 --> 00:36:03,120
but also the UK

1104
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:04,100
the US

1105
00:36:04,100 --> 00:36:04,580
Japan

1106
00:36:04,580 --> 00:36:06,799
at that time

1107
00:36:06,799 --> 00:36:07,859
early 2011

1108
00:36:07,859 --> 00:36:09,700
all of these governments

1109
00:36:09,700 --> 00:36:10,960
had massive deficits

1110
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:11,740
that were growing

1111
00:36:11,740 --> 00:36:13,620
they were selling off their assets

1112
00:36:13,620 --> 00:36:15,560
they were going into debt

1113
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:17,360
they were losing their homes

1114
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:20,020
but if the government

1115
00:36:20,020 --> 00:36:20,759
is losing

1116
00:36:20,759 --> 00:36:21,980
its assets

1117
00:36:21,980 --> 00:36:23,160
and going into debt

1118
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,500
and the people

1119
00:36:24,500 --> 00:36:25,360
are losing their assets

1120
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:26,700
and going into debt

1121
00:36:26,700 --> 00:36:29,340
then where are the assets going

1122
00:36:29,340 --> 00:36:31,000
and who's on the other side

1123
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:31,420
of the debt

1124
00:36:31,420 --> 00:36:34,360
then I looked to the right of me

1125
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:36,060
and I looked to the left of me

1126
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:37,920
and I realised I was surrounded

1127
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:39,200
by millionaires

1128
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:41,100
it was us

1129
00:36:41,100 --> 00:36:41,580
wasn't it

1130
00:36:41,580 --> 00:36:43,380
we were the balance

1131
00:36:43,380 --> 00:36:45,820
we were the boys

1132
00:36:45,820 --> 00:36:46,520
who would be richer

1133
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:47,320
than our fathers

1134
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:49,240
in a world full of kids

1135
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:49,820
who'd be poor

1136
00:36:49,820 --> 00:36:51,780
it was us

1137
00:36:51,780 --> 00:36:53,340
we were the ones

1138
00:36:53,340 --> 00:36:54,060
on the other side

1139
00:36:54,060 --> 00:36:55,340
of the Italian government debt

1140
00:36:55,340 --> 00:36:56,760
we were the ones

1141
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:57,380
on the other side

1142
00:36:57,380 --> 00:36:58,360
of Aidan's mum's mortgage

1143
00:36:58,360 --> 00:37:01,240
we would buy Assad's mum's house

1144
00:37:01,240 --> 00:37:02,300
and rent it back

1145
00:37:02,300 --> 00:37:03,960
to Assad's kids

1146
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,840
and then we would have the house

1147
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:06,980
and the debt too

1148
00:37:06,980 --> 00:37:08,380
we'd lend it back to them

1149
00:37:08,380 --> 00:37:09,440
and it would grow

1150
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:10,060
and it would grow

1151
00:37:10,060 --> 00:37:10,880
and it would compound

1152
00:37:10,880 --> 00:37:11,740
and it would compound

1153
00:37:11,740 --> 00:37:15,160
the situation wouldn't get better

1154
00:37:15,160 --> 00:37:16,640
it would get worse

1155
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:18,940
it wasn't confidence

1156
00:37:18,940 --> 00:37:20,620
it was cancer

1157
00:37:20,620 --> 00:37:23,260
it was never going to get better

1158
00:37:23,260 --> 00:37:26,460
what does that mean?

1159
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:29,780
I knew what it meant

1160
00:37:29,780 --> 00:37:31,920
it meant I had to buy

1161
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:33,080
a green euro dollar futures

1162
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:36,380
now that's the bet on interest rates

1163
00:37:36,380 --> 00:37:37,880
at that time

1164
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,160
everybody thought interest rates

1165
00:37:39,160 --> 00:37:39,660
would go up

1166
00:37:39,660 --> 00:37:40,940
but they wouldn't

1167
00:37:40,940 --> 00:37:43,700
I put that bet on a massive size

1168
00:37:43,700 --> 00:37:45,360
and by the end of the year

1169
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:47,060
I was Citibank's most profitable

1170
00:37:47,060 --> 00:37:47,860
trader in the world

1171
00:37:47,860 --> 00:37:50,200
